bug.description:
import streamlit as st import socket
@st.cache def test_cache(socket): pass
test_cache(socket.socket()) The above code throws an error because socket.socket can't be hashed by the caching function. The fix is to change the st.cache declaration to @st.cache(hash_funcs={socket.socket: id}). However, the warning we show makes no mention of hash_funcs, or the fact that it's a function parameter that's not being hashed properly. Instead, it suggests using the allow_output_mutation=True flag (which doesn't fix the issue), and also gives a lengthy explanation about adding your virtualenv to the folderBlacklist (which also doesn't fix the issue.)
